overview.what:
A decorator factory is a function that returns a decorator. Standard decorators only accept one argument (the function being decorated). To pass custom arguments to a decorator, we create an outer function that receives those arguments and returns the actual decorator.

  @retry(max_retries=3)
  def fetch_data():
      pass

This forms three nested levels: the factory (takes config), the decorator (takes the target function), and the wrapper (takes the function's arguments). Think of the factory as a machine that configures and builds a custom decorator based on the specs you give it.

